channel.title: Lost picture
channel.description: Hi, recently i saw a picture on the internet wich was of great importance but it got removed the next day and i forgot to save it. Now my question is if i could find it somewhere in my internet temporary files or doesn't it save the images that you didnt view much? I really really need to find that image.

item.title: Lost picture
item.dc:creator: @Tribal Tribal
item.description:
@Tribal wrote:

dragonus18:

i bet you could look in TIF but then agian its probly overflowing with porn and it would take hours to find it.

No , almost everything in there had to do with MSN and Hotmail.[quote=“ThAt0n36Uy, post:3, topic:135328”]You can, the easiest way I know how is with WinRAR’s file browser. just open WinRAR, hit the “…” and that should have a cache off all the pictures viewed.[/quote]

Aha! Thanks i found some more pictures with it. I’ll look for it and i’ll post if i found it or not.
Thanks again ;D
